== Roasted Carrots & Broccoli ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash
and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Cut
@broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and mince or grate
@garlic{1%clove}. Dice @Roma tomato{1} into 1⁄4-inch pieces.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add the broccoli then).

Once carrots have roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss broccoli
on empty side with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4, toss broccoli on a second baking sheet; roast broccoli on top rack and carrots on
> middle rack.

Return sheet to top rack and roast until veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Tuscan-Spiced Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp Tuscan Heat Spice instead.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken starts to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium and add a splash or two of
> water.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

== Garlic-Tomato Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and
tomato. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and softened, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, half the
@Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, @water{1/2%cup}, and a pinch of @Tuscan Heat Spice{pinch}
until melted and combined. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened,
~{1-3%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 1 cup water and about 1/3 tsp Tuscan Heat Spice.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and
pepper.

== Assembly ==

When veggies are almost done, remove sheet from oven. Carefully push broccoli into two bunches
on sheet and sprinkle with remaining Monterey Jack.

> For 4 servings, remove sheet with broccoli from oven and carefully push broccoli into four
> bunches.

Return to top rack and roast until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, broccoli, and carrots between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.